<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 52 
                    
                        Marshal Stalin to Prime
                        Minister Churchill
                    
                    Printed from a copy of a courtesy copy received by
                        the American Embassy at Moscow.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d52</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">52</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-05T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/6–645</note>
                <head>No. 52 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2" type="from">Marshal Stalin</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1" type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d52fn1">Printed from a copy of a courtesy copy received by
                        the American Embassy at Moscow.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation?]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">personal</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-05">June 5,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Arising from your message<note n="2" xml:id="d52fn2">See <ref target="#d47">document No. 47</ref>.</note> on the desirability of transferring
                    meeting of the Three to an earlier date than July 15th, I should like to say
                    once again that the date of July 15th was proposed by President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>; and I expressed agreement with that
                    date. Inasmuch as correspondence is taking place between you and President
                        <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> on this subject at the moment,
                    I shall refrain from making any new proposals about the date of our meeting.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
